
[1]anabaptist

   ANABAP'TIST, n. [Gr. again, and a baptist.]

   One who holds the doctrine of the baptism of adults, or of the
   invalidity of infant baptism, and the necessity of rebaptization in an
   adult age. One who maintains that baptism ought always to be performed
   by immersion.
